* Tutorial - Test mr-mpi-blast

   * NOTE: This tutorial is prepared and tested on XSEDE Ranger cluster.
   
   
1. Set Ranger module list

   $ bash $MRMPIBLAST_PREFIX/tutorial/ranger_setup_env.sh
   

2. Build the NCBI C++ Toolkit with mr-mpi-blast

   Please refer $MRMPIBLAST_PREFIX/README


3. Copy tutorial files to $MRMPIBLAST_PREFIX/tutorial

   $ sh $WORKING_DIR/ncbi_cxx--7_0_0/src/app/mr-mpi-blast/tutorial/install_tutorial.sh
   
   
4. Prepare test data and run test

   (1) Go to the tutorial directory
    
       $ cd $MRMPIBLAST_PREFIX/tutorial


   (2) Generate queries
       
       $ sh 1.generate_query.sh
   
        - Download NCBI RefSeq viral FASTA sequence files
        - Generate queries (1000bp length) by slitting the viral FASTA file 
        - Generate index files with the query file for running mr-mpi-blast
        
   
   (3) Make NCBI database
      
       $ sh 2.make_blastdb.sh
   
        - Download NCBI RefSeq microbial FASTA sequence files
        - Make BLAST database using "makeblastdb" utility

        
   (4) Run mr-mpi-blast
       
       * NOTE: Please set your SGE account to $SGE_ACCOUNT 
       
       $ sh 3.run_mr-mpi-blast.sh
       
        - Qsub mr-mpi-blast for BLAST search of the quries against the 
          generated BLAST db

        
   (5) Convert output hit files from mr-mpi-blast
   
       $ sh 4.convert_hits.sh
        
         - Convert *.bin files generated in $MRMPIBLAST_PREFIX/tutorial/blastdb 
           into CSV file format
         
       * NOTE: In this tutorial example, the first column in hits.csv means the 
         unique query id in viral_all_query.fa.def in which the original deflines 
         can be retrieved.

